products.title: 1/2"-13 Fluoropolymer Coated A194 2-H Heavy Hex Nut
products.notes:
Notes

The most versatile and widely used nut, it should be used with any low carbon bolt or screw that is heat-treated; heavy hex signifies larger nut casting. Grade 2H of ASTM A194/A194M. ANSI B1.1 UNC and UNF, or UN8 Class 2B thread requirement. Fluoropolymer coat is a thin film that provides excellent corrosion and chemical resistance. Fluoropolymer coating benefits include reduced friction, resistance to galling, non stick, non wetting, electrical resistance and abrasion resistance.

products.title: 1/2"-13 Grade 5 Plain Finish Steel Security Heavy Hex - Steel Insert Lock Nut
products.notes:
Notes

Security Locknuts are designed so that the insert raises away from the nut body upon application. This creates "isolation" from the load: the nut body carries the load and the insert does the locking. Security Locknuts can be adjusted, readjusted, removed, repositioned, and reused as often as required. Heat resistant up to 750 Fahrenheit. Plain Finish, or bare metal finish which may contain a light coating of oil.

products.title: 1/4"-20 ECOGUARD Finish Steel Top Lock Nut for Grade 9 Applications
products.notes:
Notes

Download EcoGuard Product Standard

Uniquely shaped threads provide a vibration resistant friction fit, so the nut stays put. These all metal locknuts withstand higher temperatures than nylon insert locknuts. Top thread section is deformed to create two or three locking zones; they start easily by hand, then must be wrenched into final position. Grade 9 is stronger than Grade C, Grade 8. ANSI B1.1 UNC or UNF Class 2B thread requirement. FNL Grade 9 Fasteners are coated with a EcoGuard Coating that meets 1000 hours of salt spray corrosion resistance.

 

  • Comes coated with an EcoGuard finish that meets 1000 hours of salt spray corrosion resistance. Also has stronger tensile strength than grade 8 fasteners.
General Fastening applications where high strength and/or superior corrosion resistance is needed.

products.notes:
Notes

TThreads are molded into the nylon insert locking the bolt into place. Nylon Insert Jam Lock Nuts typically have a cased metal outside formed into a hex pattern easily torqued by a wrench or socket; Jam Lock Nuts feature a thin pattern profile. Type NTE 18-8 Stainless Steel material. ASME B1.1 UNC and UNF Class 2B thread requirement. Stainless Steel material, because of the presence of chromium, creates an invisible surface film that resists oxidation and makes the material "passive" or corrosion resistant.

products.title: 1/4"-20 Grade 18-8 Stainless Steel Top Lock Nut
products.notes:
Notes

Uniquely shaped threads provide a vibration resistant friction fit, so the nut stays put. These all metal locknuts withstand higher temperatures than nylon insert locknuts. Top thread section is deformed to create two or three locking zones; they start easily by hand, then must be wrenched into final position. 18-8 Stainless Steel. ANSI B1.1 UNC or UNF Class 2B thread requirement. Stainless Steel material.

#4-40 Grade 18-8 Stainless Steel with External Tooth Lock Washer K-Lock Nut
products.notes:
Notes

K-Lock nuts are a general purpose nuts for moderate load assemblies. They consist of a nut assembled with a free spinning washer. The teeth pattern of the washer bite into both the nut and the base material to prevent loosening caused by vibration. 18-8 Stainless Steel nut; 400 Series martensitic series stainless steel washer. ANSI B1.1 Class 2B thread requirement. Stainless Steel material.

1/4"-20 SAE J995 Grade 2 Plain Finish Steel Slotted Hex Nut
products.notes:
Notes

Slotted Hex Nuts are hex nuts with opposed slots cut into the top of the nut. Typically the slots are cut through the center of the flats. These slots are for the insertion of a cotter type pin. Used in many applications but used specifically in automotive bearing/wheel hub to spindle assemblies. ASTM A563 Grade A. ASME B1.1 UNC and UNF Class 2B thread requirement. Plain Finish, or bare metal finish which may contain a light coating of oil.
